The '''Award of the Mechanic's Nightmare''' was a decoration of honor presented to [[Wraith Squadron]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] [[Garik Loran]] in jest following his survival of the [[Battle for the Razor's Kiss|Battle for the ''Razor's Kiss'']] in [[7 ABY/Legends|7 ABY]].

==History==
During the [[Battle for the Razor's Kiss|battle]], [[Garik Loran]] suffered heavy damage to his [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] as well as considerable damage to his own person. The canopy of his cockpit was punctured by enemy laser fire, which in turn hit him in his left side. It was something of a miracle that he survived from his injuries, much less being able to fend off the pain and the coldness of [[Vacuum/Legends|vacuum]] to first destroy a [[TIE/IN interceptor/Legends|TIE/IN interceptor]] close on the tail of fellow [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] [[Tyria Sarkin Tainer|Tyria Sarkin]], and then finding the strength to maneuver his fighter to safety.

The award itself was a gray statuette of a [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] mechanic with a wrench upraised as a weapon. The mechanic's expression was of pure, if silly, rage. The figure was half the length of a [[Human/Legends|Human]] forearm.

The award was in mock tribute to the extremely damaged state Loran's X-wing was in when returned to the [[EF76 Nebulon-B escort frigate/Legends|Nebulon-B escort frigate]] ''[[Tedevium]]'', described by [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] as, "the worst shape her mechanics had ever seen a flying [[Snubfighter/Legends|snubfighter]]." Loran himself had to be cut out of the cockpit, as part of his charred flesh had melted together with the cockpit's instrumentation.

